 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 12:26:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> Kani:  I don't see why you're so intent on permitting this little troll to do what he did.  I'm not &quot;hurt&quot; by his comments, but I am offended.  I don't think he ought to be permitted to do so around here.  I'm offended by plenty of other things that happen around here, but this kind of foolishness (especially as it breaks the forum rules) is not something that ought to be put up with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 12:33:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> This message board has rules. &nbsp;Despite the old clich&#0233;, rules are <i>not</i> there just to be broken. &nbsp;The guidelines set forth are there to keep this place a relatively welcome place for the Erollisi Marr community to post. &nbsp;Ogmuk has laid out the rules so people know there are possibilities for banning, and I've made a request because I feel it's warranted.<br>
<br>
His "blips" as you call them have the potential to make people very physically ill. &nbsp;The loss of human life and the amount of hatred being thrown around here aren't things to play around with. &nbsp;His comments aren't the typical "rouse the crowd" comments that people throw around just to start flamewars. &nbsp;People are dead. &nbsp;Many are fearing nuclear consequences. &nbsp;Joking about how this is a good thing due to "population control" or "more available jobs" is in such bad taste that I'd rather see Jevert and Inviticus running around blabbing. &nbsp;This situation doesn't just affect people in New York City; Washington, D.C.; or the other sites of crashes. &nbsp;This is nationwide, and this is worldwide. &nbsp;My friends and family in different countries are both in mourning over people they know and also anxious about what's to come. &nbsp;Multiple countries have closed down air travel and are checking their own defense statuses. &nbsp;That is how serious it is.<br>
<br>
His posts aren't "hurting" me, but they do disgust me, much the same way as someone jumping on live television with a freshly-dug up corpse and ripping pieces of its flesh out with his teeth would. &nbsp;Yeah, most of us live in a "free world." &nbsp;There is a thing called decency though, and it's one of the buttresses of that free world. &nbsp;I feel that I'm an active contributor to this message board community. &nbsp;I don't think that I should be the one to go away just because he wants to come and parade in front of us with his "hee hee look at all the death and carnage" attitude. &nbsp;Read other people's posts and you'll see they all feel the same way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalenie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salenie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 12:59:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> I do, Kanibal.  You are expressing the argument a LOT of people were making when EQ Traders Corner editted Scoppie's post to remove her .sig file.  Don't know if the same people calling for the boycott of that site are the same people calling for the banning of Mors...not quite THAT cynical enough to look up the older thread. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I'll just think 'what goes around comes around'.<br>
