</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucaladdor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladdor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=9311062&img=5" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 517<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 1:03:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> If he signed with his ingame name or real life name/adress/email he would be a fucking sad individual, but by posting anonomously he's nothing other than a troll with very bad taste<br>
<br>
If he would back his posts up by letting people know who he was i could see the case you're arguing Kani ... but not when he's too cowardly to show who he is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 1:08:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> It doesn't matter how strongly we feel about our own opinions. &nbsp;We'd rather not need something horrible or disgusting to be the only means of bringing us together under beliefs or causes. &nbsp;There's another thing that goes hand-in-hand with freedom. &nbsp;That's <i>peace</i>. &nbsp;Sure, blood was shed for that freedom, and more will be shed to keep it. &nbsp;To be truly free though, we have to be <i>safe</i> and free... <i>happy</i> and free.<br>
<br>
There's something else you keep forgetting though. &nbsp;This particular board is Ogmuk's territory. &nbsp;It may belong to ezboard, but he's administering it. &nbsp;It's something of a benevolent dictatorship, not a democracy. &nbsp;In most cases, his word is final. &nbsp;However, I guarantee you that if someone comes here and starts preaching about attacking America (in a serious manner, not like our Canadian neighbors always talk), that the person will be chased off the boards. &nbsp;It's not a <i>right</i> to post here, it's a <i>priviledge</i> granted by ezboard, Ogmuk, and the Erollisi Marr community.<br>
<br>
You're trying to say that buttnuggets like him are making us stronger, and that we're trying to squash his right of free speech. &nbsp;There are limits to that right of free speech, outlined heavily with the idea of common decency. &nbsp;"That which doesn't kill me blahblahblah..." &nbsp;I'd rather stay a little weaker if it means I don't have to put up with this crap. &nbsp;I'd prefer not to get anymore jaded than I already am.<br>
<br>
It's really odd that you're defending him so much. &nbsp;He's continuing to play it off like a big joke, which should tell you he's not trying to make people believe "his opinion." &nbsp;He's just being inappropriate and enjoying it.<br>
<br>
This isn't an issue of freedom of speech. &nbsp;It's an issue of decency and compassion. &nbsp;There are dozens of people here on these boards who are seeking moral support from each other. &nbsp;Simply put, that trash <b>does not belong here.</b> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 2:13:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> But anonymously?  Forget the moronic and offensive nature of what he said, he did it anonymously.  None of the rest of us are doing so.  I'm sorry that you can't seem to see the difference between suppressing an actual opinion and suppressing idiocy that is only intended to incite. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 2:15:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> No, I don't think anyone is going to train him. &nbsp;The reason people are bringing his in-game up is because we want the turd gone. &nbsp;He doesn't have the nerve to say stuff like this if people recognized him in the game, because he's fully aware that it's going to hurt some and offend almost everyone.<br>
<br>
